          "headersSize": 573,
          "httpVersion": "HTTP/1.1",
          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"faq\",\"description\":\"\\n            Use this tool when the user is asking questions about Google Ads, how the ad builder works, or seeking clarification about headlines, descriptions, callouts, structured snippets, or keywords.\\n            \\n            This tool searches the FAQ database and returns relevant Q&A pairs to help answer the user's question.  When using this tool, respond conversationally with just text - do NOT include any JSON or structured data.\\n        \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"The user's question or search query\"}},\"required\":[\"query\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Let's start building your ad! I drafted a few headlines and descriptions that meet Google's requirements.\\n\\nGoogle will mix and match them to find what performs best. We can tailor them together to make them feel just right for you.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Stop Scheduling Back-and-Forth\\\",\\n    \\\"Find Meeting Times in Seconds\\\",\\n    \\\"Meetings Across Time Zones?\\\",\\n    \\\"80% Less Scheduling Time\\\",\\n    \\\"Instant Meeting Coordination\\\",\\n    \\\"Your Team's Scheduling Problem Solved\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"descriptions\\\": [\\n    \\\"Connect calendars, set preferences, done. We find times that work for everyone instantly. Join 2,000+ teams saving 15 hours weekly.\\\",\\n    \\\"Tired of endless Slack threads about meeting times? Our AI suggests optimal slots across all time zones automatically.\\\",\\n    \\\"Stop wasting time coordinating. Get your free demo today and see how distributed teams cut scheduling by 80%.\\\",\\n    \\\"Used by TechCorp and thousands of remote teams. Eliminate calendar chaos—try it free for 14 days. No credit card needed.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"What are structured snippets?\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015NvTGjnsEu5KbbXs4mYQJa\",\"name\":\"faq\",\"input\":{\"query\":\"What are structured snippets in Google Ads\"}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"[1] Q: What are \\\"Product or Service Offerings\\\" on this page?\\nA: This section represents Structured Snippet Assets in Google Ads.\\nThey show as:\\nA category label (such as \\\"Services\\\" or \\\"Styles\\\")\\nFollowed by a list of values (the items you offer)\\nExample:\\nServices: In-Studio Portraits, Outdoor Sessions, Holiday Cards\\nThese snippets:\\nHelp customers quickly see the range of what you offer.\\nMake your ad look more complete and trustworthy.\\n(Section: Product or Service Offerings (Structured Snippet Assets))\\n\\n[2] Q: How does this Content page relate to the \\\"Highlights\\\" tab?\\nA: On the Content tab you write the main ad text that appears in almost every impression.\\nOn the Highlights tab (next step):\\nYou will usually add structured information such as features, service types, or callouts, depending on the configuration.\\nThese often map to Google ad extensions (now called \\\"assets\\\"), which can show in addition to your headlines and descriptions.\\nYou should complete the Content tab first, since this is the foundation of your ad.\\n(Section: Content Structure)\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015NvTGjnsEu5KbbXs4mYQJa\"}]}],\"system\":\"<background>\\n        You are a helpful marketing consultant who helps users test their business ideas.\\n        The process consists of 3 steps:\\n        1. Brainstorm a killer new business idea\\n        2. Design a landing page with killer marketing copy\\n        3. Launch an ads campaign to drive traffic — and see if people are excited to buy!\\n    </background>\\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            Users have already completed:\\n                1. Brainstorming\\n                2. Designing their landing page\\n\\n            Now we're helping them:\\n                3. Build a Google ads campaign to drive traffic to their new website\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are an expert Google Ads copywriter helping to create compelling ad extensions for a business.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <asset_generation_instructions>\\n            Generate the following assets:\\n\\n                1. Generate the following assets for this business's Google Ads campaign:\\n\\n        <asset_instructions>\\n            <instruction index=\\\"1\\\">1: ## Unique Features (Callouts)\\n            Generate 6 unique selling points that highlight why customers should choose this business. These appear as callout extensions in Google Ads.\\n\\n            **Guidelines:**\\n            - Keep each feature concise and punchy (typically 12-25 characters)\\n            - Focus on competitive advantages, special offers, or key differentiators\\n            - Use action-oriented language when possible\\n            - Examples: \\\"Free Fast Delivery\\\", \\\"10% Student Discount\\\", \\\"30-Day Free Returns\\\", \\\"No Obligation Estimate\\\", \\\"35+ Years Experience\\\", \\\"Family Owned\\\"\\n\\n            **Requirements:**\\n            - Generate exactly 6 unique features\\n            - Each must be 25 characters or less\\n            - Avoid generic phrases - be specific to this business\\n            - Focus on tangible benefits or proof points\\n\\n            Remember: These highlights make the ad larger and give potential customers more reasons to click. Make them compelling, specific, and relevant to the business's unique value proposition.</instruction>\\n<instruction index=\\\"2\\\">2: ## Product or Service Offerings (Structured Snippets)\\n            Generate a category header and 3 specific examples of what this business offers. These appear as structured snippet extensions in Google Ads.\\n\\n            **Category Header:**\\n            Choose ONE header that best describes what you're listing (e.g., \\\"Types\\\", \\\"Services\\\", \\\"Amenities\\\", \\\"Products\\\", \\\"Styles\\\", \\\"Brands\\\", \\\"Courses\\\", \\\"Destinations\\\")\\n\\n            **Details (Values):**\\n            List 3 specific offerings under that category header.\\n            - Examples: \\n              - Types: \\\"Web Design\\\", \\\"SEO\\\", \\\"Content Marketing\\\"\\n              - Amenities: \\\"Free WiFi\\\", \\\"Free Parking\\\", \\\"Included Breakfast\\\", \\\"Spa Services\\\"\\n              - Services: \\\"Emergency Repairs\\\", \\\"Annual Maintenance\\\", \\\"Free Estimates\\\"\\n\\n            **Requirements:**\\n            - Choose an appropriate category header\\n            - Generate exactly 3 specific, relevant details\\n            - Do not generate more than 3 details\\n            - Each detail should be 25 characters or less\\n            - Be specific to this business's actual offerings</instruction>\\n        </asset_instructions>\\n\\n                2. Format your response with:\\n                    - First, a brief introduction (1-2 sentences) using this template: \\\"Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\\"\\n                    - Then, a JSON code block with the structured data\\n        </asset_generation_instructions>\\n\\n        <business_context>\\n            Idea: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones. Eliminates the back-and-forth of calendar coordination.\\n\\n            Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents. Project managers tired of endless Slack threads about 'when works for everyone?'\\n\\n            Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\n\\n            Social Proof: Used by 2,000+ distributed teams who've cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Companies like TechCorp save 15 hours per week on scheduling alone.\\n        </business_context>\\n\\n            <example_response>\\n\\n        Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\n\\n        ```json\\n        {\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"Feature 1\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 2\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 3\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 4\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 5\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 6\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"structuredSnippets\\\": {\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"Types\\\",\\n    \\\"details\\\": [\\n      \\\"Detail 1\\\",\\n      \\\"Detail 2\\\",\\n      \\\"Detail 3\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n        ```\\n\\n            </example_response>\"}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1410,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1410,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01XGH8xsAei2aWoB49aCXAFS\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Structured snippets** are a type of Google Ads extension that help showcase what your business offers.\\n\\nHere's how they work:\\n\\n**Structure:**\\n- A **category label** (like \\\"Services,\\\" \\\"Types,\\\" \\\"Amenities,\\\" \\\"Products,\\\" etc.)\\n- Followed by **3 specific items** you offer under that category\\n\\n**Example:**\\nFor a photography business, it might look like:\\n- **Services:** In-Studio Portraits, Outdoor Sessions, Holiday Cards\\n\\n**Why they matter:**\\n- They help customers quickly see the range of what you offer\\n- They make your ad look more complete and trustworthy\\n- They take up more real estate on the search results page, making your ad more prominent\\n- They give people more reasons to click\\n\\nFor your scheduling tool, we could use something like:\\n- **Services:** Calendar Integration, Time Zone Matching, Instant Suggestions\\n\\nThis tells potential customers exactly what features they'll get, right in the ad itself. Ready to create your structured snippets?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2439,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":227,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
