            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1659,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01MimJNxCKkfxi26dAsMYZ1n\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! Yes, you can absolutely change your ads after they're live. Here's what you need to know:\\n\\n**You can edit your Headlines and Descriptions** — any changes you make will sync to Google Ads. However, there are a couple of things to keep in mind:\\n\\n1. **Google may need time to re-learn** — When you make changes to your Headlines or Details, Google's algorithm may need some time to figure out which new combinations perform best. This could restart the \\\"learning phase\\\" for your campaign.\\n\\n2. **Your performance data is preserved** — The good news is that all your previous performance data stays in Google, so you're not losing any historical insights.\\n\\n3. **Make focused changes** — Small, targeted edits usually work better than completely rewriting everything at once. Unless you're repositioning your entire offer, it's better to tweak specific elements rather than overhauling the whole ad.\\n\\nSo if you launch your campaign and realize something isn't resonating with your audience, or you want to test a different angle, you can definitely make those adjustments. Just be strategic about it and avoid making massive changes all at once.\\n\\nWould you like help refining any of your ad copy before or after launch?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1481,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":267,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
