            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"faq\",\"description\":\"\\n            Use this tool when the user is asking questions about Google Ads, how the ad builder works, or seeking clarification about headlines, descriptions, callouts, structured snippets, or keywords.\\n            \\n            This tool searches the FAQ database and returns relevant Q&A pairs to help answer the user's question.  When using this tool, respond conversationally with just text - do NOT include any JSON or structured data.\\n        \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"The user's question or search query\"}},\"required\":[\"query\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Can I change my ads after they're live?\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01GXkvN88mMgKPgWuCvRi77g\",\"name\":\"faq\",\"input\":{\"query\":\"Can I change my ads after they're live?\"}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"[1] Q: Will changing my content later affect my campaign?\\nA: Yes. When you edit Headlines or Details after launch:\\nWe will sync the changes to Google Ads.\\nGoogle may need some time to re-learn which combinations perform best.\\nYour previous performance data stays in Google, but the \\\"learning\\\" phase may restart for new content.\\nSmall, focused changes are usually better than rewriting everything at once unless you are repositioning your offer.\\n(Section: General Content Page Questions)\\n\\n[2] Q: How does Launch10's AI create Details? Can I change them?\\nA: We use your earlier answers (business info, customers, offer, tone), your landing page copy, and your selected headlines to generate description options that reinforce your main value proposition, stay within character limits, and use clear calls to action\\nYou can fully edit each Detail. Your edits take priority over AI suggestions and will be used for the final ad.\\n(Section: Details)\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01GXkvN88mMgKPgWuCvRi77g\"}]}],\"system\":\"You are a helpful assistant that can answer questions about the ad creation process.\"}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1258,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1258,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01WbsJ1xVd1jaULoPgXRXCRu\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Yes, you can change your ads after they're live! Here's what you should know:\\n\\n**What happens when you edit:**\\n- Your changes will be synced to Google Ads\\n- Google may need some time to re-learn which ad combinations perform best\\n- Your previous performance data is preserved in Google, but the \\\"learning\\\" phase may restart for new content\\n\\n**Best practices for editing:**\\n- **Small, focused changes** are usually better than rewriting everything at once\\n- Only do major rewrites if you're repositioning your offer\\n- You can fully edit any part of your ads, including headlines and descriptions\\n\\nSo feel free to make adjustments to optimize your ads, but try to be strategic about it. If you're just fine-tuning based on performance data, smaller changes will help Google's system continue learning from your existing data more smoothly.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":986,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":185,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
