        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1679,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1679,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_016eYMN1tr5nTPN8KpQpf5vo\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Descriptions** are the text lines that appear below your headlines in Google Ads search results.\\n\\nHere are the key things to know about descriptions:\\n\\n**What they do:**\\n- Provide more detail about your offer and value proposition\\n- Give you space to explain benefits, features, and calls to action\\n- Help convince people to click on your ad\\n\\n**The rules:**\\n- Each description can be **up to 90 characters** (strict limit)\\n- Google usually shows **up to 2 description lines** in a single ad\\n- They appear below your headlines in search results\\n\\n**What to include:**\\n- Expand on what you mentioned in the headlines\\n- Highlight key benefits or features\\n- Include a clear call-to-action (like \\\"Call now,\\\" \\\"Get a quote,\\\" \\\"Learn more\\\")\\n- Use natural language that feels conversational\\n\\nThink of it this way: **Headlines grab attention**, and **descriptions convince people to click** by giving them a reason why they should care about your business.\\n\\nFor your scheduling tool, descriptions might highlight things like \\\"Cut meeting coordination time by 80%\\\" or \\\"Works across all time zones—no more scheduling headaches.\\\"\\n\\nReady to create your descriptions? I can draft some compelling ones that follow Google's requirements!\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2381,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":276,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
