        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1456,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1456,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01UBRHaRSYJrx84Xet8AgrLQ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! Yes, you can see your headlines in a preview! \\n\\nAccording to Google Ads, there's an **Ad Preview card** at the top of the page that:\\n\\n✅ **Updates in real-time** as you edit your headlines and descriptions  \\n✅ **Shows a sample combination** of your content so you can visualize how it looks  \\n✅ **Helps you check** for typos, tone, and overall messaging\\n\\n**Important to know:** The preview shows *one possible version* of your ad. Google will actually mix and match your headlines and descriptions in different combinations to test what performs best. So different customers might see different combinations than what appears in the preview.\\n\\nThe preview is really useful for:\\n- Making sure everything looks good and reads well\\n- Catching any typos or formatting issues\\n- Getting a feel for the overall tone and messaging\\n\\nWould you like me to generate those headlines and descriptions for your scheduling tool now? Once I do, you'll be able to see them in that preview and we can refine them together if needed!\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2392,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":232,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
          "cookies": [],
          "headers": [
            {
              "name": "anthropic-organization-id",
              "value": "24f20592-edc6-4419-b580-2d283f97eae2"
