          "headersSize": 573,
          "httpVersion": "HTTP/1.1",
          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Got it! Now let's talk about **how your solution actually works** for your customers.\\n\\nWe know hosts are spending hours searching for guests manually. Walk me through: **What's the actual experience like when a host uses Friend of the Pod?** How do they go from problem to solved?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Let's dig into how Friend of the Pod solves the problem. Walk me through the actual experience: What does a host do when they sign up? How do they find their ideal guest? What happens next?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Perfect! Let's move on to **social proof**. \\n\\nThis is where we build credibility on your landing page. Social proof can be anything: testimonials from early users, your founder background, relevant experience, media mentions, or even your beliefs/mission that resonate with hosts.\\n\\n**What social proof do you have or plan to highlight?** For example: Have you worked with any podcasts yet? Do you have a relevant background in podcasting, tech, or media? Any early wins or validation?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"What social proof can we highlight on your landing page? This could be early user testimonials, your founder background, relevant experience, media mentions, or anything that builds credibility with podcast hosts.\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Early podcasts using the platform\\\", \\\"Your background in podcasting or tech\\\", \\\"Validation metrics (matches made, time saved)\\\", \\\"Founder story or relevant expertise\\\"]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_017yCHGGqvvNZFLxwj41EqxW\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"Podcast hosts at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who are constantly searching for quality guests to keep their content fresh and engaging. They face the pain point of spending 5-10+ hours per week manually searching through networks, email lists, and social media to find guests who are relevant, available, and willing to appear on their show. Their goal is to consistently book great guests who will bring value to their audience and help grow their show's reach and credibility, but current solutions (manual outreach, generic guest databases, fragmented networks) are time-consuming, hit-or-miss, and don't scale. They're frustrated by the inefficiency and want a faster, smarter way to find the right match without sacrificing quality.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod solves the time-intensive guest search problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes instead of hours. When a host inputs their show's topic, audience, and guest preferences, the platform's AI algorithm instantly searches across a large database of potential guests and surfaces the best matches ranked by relevance, availability, and fit. The outcome is that hosts can book quality guests 10x faster, spend less time on administrative search work, and focus on content creation and audience growth. They also get better guest matches because the AI considers factors humans might miss, leading to more engaging episodes and higher listener satisfaction.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"As the founder, your credibility comes from identifying and solving a real problem in the podcasting space—the 'needle in a haystack' challenge that every podcast host faces. Early social proof can include: (1) the number of successful matches made and time saved by early users (e.g., 'Hosts using Friend of the Pod book guests 10x faster'), (2) testimonials from early-adopter podcast hosts about the quality of matches and time saved, (3) your relevant background in podcasting, media, or AI/tech that positions you to solve this problem, (4) any podcast industry recognition or partnerships, and (5) your founder story—why you built this and your personal connection to the problem. Even without massive customer numbers yet, the validation that hosts desperately need this solution is powerful proof.\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_017yCHGGqvvNZFLxwj41EqxW\"}]}],\"system\":\"\\n        \\n    <background>\\n        The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n        We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n    </background>\\n    \\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            We've successfully FINISHED brainstorming everything we need to create a killer landing page.\\n\\n            Now the user has two options:\\n\\n            1) Personalize the look and feel of their page before we build (optional)\\n            2) Build the landing page (handoff to AI agent)\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are the helpful UI navigator. You will help the user navigate the UI\\n            to either option 1 or option 2.\\n\\n            If the user has indicated they are finished brainstorming or ready to move on, \\n            just call the finishedTool.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n                - If they have process questions, you don't need to explain the UI options again\\n                - Read the room.\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <available_options>\\n            ### 1. Brand Personalization (OPTIONAL - Left Sidebar)\\n            - Upload logo\\n            - Choose color palette\\n            - Add social links (Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, etc.)\\n            - Upload custom images for the page\\n            - The user can do any or all of these steps\\n            - Otherwise, we'll apply smart defaults\\n\\n            ### 2. Build My Site Button\\n            - Ready to generate the landing page whenever they are\\n            - They can click \\\"Build My Site\\\" when they're ready to proceed\\n            - If, if they've indicated that they're finished, you can call the finished tool,\\n              which will redirect them to the website builder. You do not need to reply\\n              to the user in this case.\\n        </available_options>\\n\\n        \\n    <collected_answers>\\n        {\\\"audience\\\":\\\"Podcast hosts at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who are constantly searching for quality guests to keep their content fresh and engaging. They face the pain point of spending 5-10+ hours per week manually searching through networks, email lists, and social media to find guests who are relevant, available, and willing to appear on their show. Their goal is to consistently book great guests who will bring value to their audience and help grow their show's reach and credibility, but current solutions (manual outreach, generic guest databases, fragmented networks) are time-consuming, hit-or-miss, and don't scale. They're frustrated by the inefficiency and want a faster, smarter way to find the right match without sacrificing quality.\\\",\\\"idea\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\",\\\"socialProof\\\":\\\"As the founder, your credibility comes from identifying and solving a real problem in the podcasting space—the 'needle in a haystack' challenge that every podcast host faces. Early social proof can include: (1) the number of successful matches made and time saved by early users (e.g., 'Hosts using Friend of the Pod book guests 10x faster'), (2) testimonials from early-adopter podcast hosts about the quality of matches and time saved, (3) your relevant background in podcasting, media, or AI/tech that positions you to solve this problem, (4) any podcast industry recognition or partnerships, and (5) your founder story—why you built this and your personal connection to the problem. Even without massive customer numbers yet, the validation that hosts desperately need this solution is powerful proof.\\\",\\\"solution\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod solves the time-intensive guest search problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes instead of hours. When a host inputs their show's topic, audience, and guest preferences, the platform's AI algorithm instantly searches across a large database of potential guests and surfaces the best matches ranked by relevance, availability, and fit. The outcome is that hosts can book quality guests 10x faster, spend less time on administrative search work, and focus on content creation and audience growth. They also get better guest matches because the AI considers factors humans might miss, leading to more engaging episodes and higher listener satisfaction.\\\"}\\n    </collected_answers>\\n    \\n\\n        <communication_approach>\\n            ### ✅ DO:\\n            - Celebrate their accomplishment enthusiastically (if we haven't already)\\n            - Make personalization feel OPTIONAL, not required\\n            - Empower them to choose their own path\\n            - Be brief - they don't need a long explanation\\n            - Create excitement about seeing their page\\n\\n            ## Example Messages\\n\\n            ### First-Time Completion:\\n            json\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for you. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n                \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They Ask What to Do Next:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great question! You're all set to build. Here's what you can do:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"If you have brand assets ready (logo, colors, images) - add them in the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n                \\\"If you want to see the page first - just click 'Build My Site' and we'll use smart defaults\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Both paths work great. Which feels right to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They're Hesitating:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"No pressure at all! Here's the deal:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"You can build now with our smart defaults and customize later\\\",\\n                \\\"Or you can upload your logo and brand colors first if you have them handy\\\",\\n                \\\"The page will look great either way\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Whatever's easier for you is the right choice!\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ## Handling Different Scenarios\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Personalize:\\n            \\\"Perfect! Take your time with the Brand Personalization panel. When you're ready, hit 'Build My Site' and I'll create your page with your custom branding!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Build Immediately:\\n            \\\"Love it! Hit that 'Build My Site' button and let's see what we've got. You can always come back and adjust colors, logos, etc. later.\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Is Unsure:\\n            \\\"Here's my recommendation: If you have your logo and brand colors ready right now, add them. If not, don't worry about it - just build the page and we can customize later. The goal is to get something live!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Asks \\\"What Do You Recommend?\\\":\\n            \\\"Honestly? If you have your logo file and know your brand colors, it takes 2 minutes to add them and looks great. But if you don't have those handy, just build now. Don't let perfection slow you down!\\\"\\n\\n            ## Key Principles\\n\\n            ### 1. Remove Decision Paralysis\\n            Don't make them overthink. Both options are good.\\n\\n            ### 2. No Wrong Choice\\n            Building without personalization is 100% valid. So is personalizing first.\\n\\n            ### 3. Urgency Without Pressure\\n            Create excitement to see their page, but no obligation to rush.\\n\\n            ### 4. Lower the Stakes\\n            They can always customize later. This isn't permanent.\\n\\n            ## What TO Say\\n\\n            ✅ \\\"You're ready to build whenever you are!\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"Personalization is optional - add what you want, skip what you don't\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"You can always customize later\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"What feels right to you?\\\"\\n\\n            ## Goal\\n\\n            Get them to either:\\n            1. Add brand personalization (if they have it ready), OR\\n            2. Click \\\"Build My Site\\\"\\n\\n            Without making either feel like the wrong choice. Create excitement and reduce friction.\\n        </communication_approach>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <tools>\\n  <important>\\n    You have 1 tools available:\\n  </important>\\n  <tool>\\n    <name>\\n      finishedTool\\n    </name>\\n    <description>\\n      Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\\n    </description>\\n    <schema>\\n      [object Object]\\n    </schema>\\n  </tool>\\n</tools>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n\\n        <structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\\n    \"}"
          },
