        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2412,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2412,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01CtCvWBHoQ2Wot4BNUWzGVq\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"helpMe\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Perfect! Let me help you get specific about who you're selling to and what keeps them up at night.\\\",\\n  \\\"template\\\": \\\"**1. Who are they?**\\\\n[Job title/role] at [company size/type] who [specific context about their work]\\\\n\\\\n**2. What's their main pain point?**\\\\nThey spend [time/effort] on [specific task], which [emotional impact: frustrates/exhausts/delays them]\\\\n\\\\n**3. What are they actually trying to achieve?**\\\\nThey want to [specific outcome] so they can [bigger goal/benefit]\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why doesn't this work today?**\\\\nCurrent solutions [describe the gap: too manual, too expensive, too slow, etc.]\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"**1. Who are they?** Podcast hosts with 5K-50K listeners who run shows solo or with a small team\\\\n\\\\n**2. What's their main pain point?** They spend 3-5 hours per week hunting for guests on LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists, which leaves them exhausted and frustrated because they'd rather spend that time on actual production\\\\n\\\\n**3. What are they trying to achieve?** They want to book quality guests consistently so they can focus on growing their audience and building their brand as a thought leader\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why doesn't this work today?** Finding the right guest fit is manual and scattered—there's no centralized place to search, so they waste time on bad leads and rejections\\\",\\n    \\\"**1. Who are they?** B2B SaaS founders and marketing leaders who use podcasts as a growth channel\\\\n\\\\n**2. What's their main pain point?** They struggle to find guests who align with their audience and have actual credibility, wasting weeks on outreach that goes nowhere\\\\n\\\\n**3. What are they trying to achieve?** They want a steady pipeline of interesting guests so they can maintain a consistent publishing schedule without the recruiting headache\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why doesn't this work today?** Manual outreach is slow and hit-or-miss; they either get no responses or book people who don't fit\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2807,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":520,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
