            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1299,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01SrtjfHFPwYBWPRtmar9GjG\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I love the concept! Podcast matchmaking is a fresh angle. But I need to understand what makes **Friend of the Pod** different from just... finding podcasts or podcast directories.\\n\\nLet me dig in:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great start! Now help me understand the differentiation. When you say 'matchmaking service'—what specifically are you matching? And what makes your approach different from existing podcast discovery tools or platforms?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"We match listeners to podcasts based on their personality type and listening habits (not just genre)\\\",\\n    \\\"We match podcast hosts with guest experts who are perfect fits for their audience\\\",\\n    \\\"We match brands with podcasts that align with their values and audience demographics\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What's the unique angle that makes Friend of the Pod stand out?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2299,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":199,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
